Package eu.advance.logistics.flow.engine.api.core

Contains the API core classes and interfaces which are somewhat independent.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Copyable<T>
    Indicates if an object can create a deep copy of itself.
    HasPassword
    Interface indicating the record contains a password field which must be managed via care.
    Identifiable<K>
    Represents classes which can be asked for their unique identifier.
    Pool<T>
    Represents a generic pooling object which supplies and takes back objects.
    PoolManager<T>
    The pool manager interface for creating, verifying and closing objects.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AdvanceData
    Convenience utils to extract or create values from various default ADVANCE XElement objects.
    BoundedPool<T>
    A bounded object pool.
    UnlimitedPool<T>
    A pool manager which may return an unlimited amount of objects.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    AdvanceAccessDenied
    Exception to indicate the user has no right to perform the operation.
    AdvanceControlException
    The base exception for the ADVANCE Flow Engine Control API.
    MultiIOException
    An exception which wraps many other exception under a common IOException-type.
